Tavatron quickened her pace when Dinobot let loose his wild roar. The sound 
sending chills down her spine, perhaps she had gone a little too far. She 
then caught a look of anger in his usually emotionless eyes. Tavatron 
growled softly, this could definitely be a problem.

Tavatron saw Dinobot's muscles tense as he snapped just inches behind her. 
His metallic jaws making a frightening snap as he nearly caught her tail. 
Tavatron howled when he clipped her fur. Enough was enough, no one snapped 
her fur and got away with it! However, when Dinobot failed to do any real 
damage Tavatron relaxed. If he had desired to do so Dinobot could've easily 
overtaken and knocked her to the ground. So, this was all some sort of 
elaborate game. She wasn't one to turn down a challenge:

"Or perhaps it is I that looks better than you!" Tavatron spun around and 
snapped at Dinbot's snout, centemeters from his own snapping jaws. She 
pulled back and growled playfully as she ran towards the ark, the massive 
doors looming before them. She pushed the door open with her front paws and 
dropped to the ground, edging her way into the ark through the partially 
opened doors. She looked behind her, waiting for Dinobot:

"We're late for the meeting..." Tavatron thought for a moment, insults 
weren't really her specialty but she was willing to give it a shot. Tavatron 
thought back to how Dinobot had nearly clipped her tail just moments ago. 
Clipperface? no, that was just stupid. No, not clipped, chop:

"C'mon Chopperface. Let's go." Tavatron smiled and gestured toward the War 
Room with her head. So it wasn't her best comment, it was better than 
nothing! Besides, Chopperface seemed to fit.
